      • getTerms

        public com.google.common.collect.ImmutableSet<ModelTerm> getTerms()

        Returns an unmodifiable set of all of the ModelTerms.

        If you want to modify the set of terms, you must use one of the above type-specific accessors like getBooleanTerms(). The different types of ModelTerms are provided via different accessors due to Hibernate's lack of support for polymorphic ElementCollections (HHH-1910).

        Returns:
        an ImmutableSet

      • getRequiredVariables

        public com.google.common.collect.ImmutableSet<Variable> getRequiredVariables()

        Returns the set of all Variables required for the model.

        Note that Variables define equality as identity, so two different Variable instances with exactly the same attributes may be put into the Set.

        Returns:
        an ImmutableSet
